tear gas police department: Hi Rebecca, Yes, tear gas has been used once by our department in one protest. The protestors were attempting to get onto the interstate (Interstate 10), which is near a tunnel with high traffic volume and high speeds.  Our law enforcement agency supports peaceful protests. It is also equally our duty to ensure the safety of protestors.  Allowing the protestors onto the interstate would have placed them in harm's way. It would have impeded the flow of traffic where protestors and motorists could have gotten injured. In this situation, the potential loss of life outweighed the risk of deploying gas. \ Charlette M. Solis, Public Affairs Manager / City of Mobile Police Department / Office of the Chief / Desk: 251-208-1918 | Cell: 251-300-7612

The circumstances involved a peaceful demonstration that unfortunately later became riotous.  The decision to utilize chemical agents followed repeated assaults by rocks, bottles and other items thrown at citizens, vehicles, officers and buildings. Some of the rioters began breaking windows to city buildings, damaging property and blocking commuters. One of the subjects also began approaching  City Hall with a gas can during these violent acts.
